benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/catalog - Delete all versions for a per tenant catalog

covered: Valid deletion scenarios are covered (TC01, TC02, TC15) with 204 responses and actual deletion of catalog versions.
Authorization and header validation are covered (TC03, TC04, TC07, TC11, TC14) including missing header, invalid token, and invalid header values; extra headers do not block deletion (TC08).
Non-existent resource handling is covered: tenant with no catalog versions (TC05) and non-existent tenant (TC06).
Performance/stress scenario is covered (TC10) with large number of versions.
Data integrity/regression scenario is covered (TC12) ensuring no orphaned references.
Robustness to request body presence is covered (TC15) noting the body is ignored.
gaps: Soft delete semantics (whether deletions are hard vs soft) are not tested.
Rate limiting/throttling scenarios are not tested.
Caching behavior/testing (ETag, Cache-Control) is not tested.
Explicit 403 forbidden path for insufficient permissions (tests focus on 401/400/204) is not clearly covered.
Policy clarification gap for non-existent catalog on an existing tenant (e.g., 204 vs 404) could use explicit tests to confirm expected behavior across edge cases.
Additional edge cases around content-type misalignments or unsupported HTTP nuances are not covered.
recommendations: Add a test to verify soft-delete semantics if applicable (no hard vs soft delete distinction in API behavior).
Introduce rate-limiting/throttling tests to ensure the endpoint behaves correctly under bursty load.
Add tests to verify caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and caching behavior for DELETE responses if applicable.
Add an explicit 403 test to cover insufficient permissions (authenticated user without delete rights).
Clarify and test policy for non-existent catalog on an existing tenant with explicit 204 vs 404 expectation, and include a dedicated test accordingly.
Include tests for additional edge cases such as content-type mismatches or unusual/invalid request bodies to ensure robustness.
